Today, I voted to keep the government open and working for the American people. 

H.R. 5371 will prevent a government shutdown while Congress works to responsibly finish the appropriations process. 

@HouseGOP remains committed to delivering real results for families and communities nationwide.

Policies that refuse to acknowledge basic biological differences between men and women take away opportunities for young girls to succeed, like those who competed in the CIF state qualifier this past weekend. We cannot allow this to keep happening. 

I will continue working with the White House and my colleagues in Congress to ensure female athletes can compete fairly and safely across all sports. 

@GavinNewsom, will you help us protect these young women and restore fair competition for them on the field of play?
